<Author>georgec456
<Content>Horrible Hotel - Worst Hyatt I've Ever Stayed At I recently went on a cruise out of Miami so I needed a place to stay the night before.I checked the rates for various hotels near the port and the Hyatt had a great rate so I booked a mini suite.After staying at this terrible hotel I wish I'd paid $50 more and stayed at the much better Intercontinental.When I first arrived at the hotel I had a good first impression of the place - the lobby was fairly elegant and everything looked somewhat upscale. On the other hand, the check in was VERY SLOW. There were 2-3 people in front of us - not a long line, but nothing was moving! There was one slow employee behind the desk who seemed to be very inefficient. After a few minutes and no movement in line, I decided to get more employees to the front desk. I politely asked some employees from the concierge desk to help with the check in process. That seemed to speed things up. By the time I was checked in I had waited 20 minutes which is inexcusable considering there were only 2 or 3 people in front of me.After checking in I immediately headed up to the room on the 10th floor. When I got out of the elevator I noticed a weird smell. The easiest way to describe it is A sunscreen smell. It wasn't a horrible smell, but a four star Hyatt shouldn't have a weird smell.When I arrived at my suite it was very warm. I immediately set the a/c to 60 hoping that it would cool down by the time I got back from dinner. I was wrong. It was warm all night. Even the hallways were freezing compared to room.Another problem I noticed was that the bathroom sink drain was not working. It was obviously just clogged. When we left for dinner I stopped by the front desk and asked them to have someone fix it. It was never fixed. Good thing we were just staying for one night. We decided to just put up with it.Even though we were on the 10th floor, the noise was terrible. There was a draw bridge on our side of the hotel that went up and down all night with the ding ding ding sound of the railroad type warning signal that you would hear near train tracks. I didn't fall asleep until very very late at night/early morning because the damn bridge went up and down all night with the loud warning signal for the cars. Also, there were cars that would occasionally honk. It's pathetic that on the 10th floor you can still hear too much noise!!!!!!!!! After getting no sleep, having a clogged sink, a weird smell in the hall, slow check in, cheap shower head THERE'S REALLY NOTHING GOOD TO SAY ABOUT THIS HOTEL! If I had to pick one pro to this hotel, it would be that it was safe. But that's it. This hotel sucks!It's truly too bad because this one Hyatt will make me think twice before booking another Hyatt in the future. I will be calling them soon to request a refund as it's unacceptable that a four star hotel could be this bad. They put my vacation to a bad start. DO NOT GO TO THIS HOTEL. I've stayed at nicer two star hotels where at least you can get a good nights sleep. 
