<Author>sam629
<Content>good but noisy construction My husband and I stayed at this hotel while attending a convention in Miami. The hotel itselt was fine--even good--but the noise level from the construction all around was really quite bothersome. On the days we left the hotel prior to 8:00am and returned after 7:00pm, we experienced no noise. However, even on Saturday morning, there was construction. That being said, our room was large and, had there not been construction, I think we would have enjoyed the view of the bay. We had a great, comfy king size bed with clean linens and a nice fluffy duvet, a pullout coach, coffee table, desk, and chair. While the hotel doesn't want to change the towels and the sheets, we requested the towels changed daily and the sheets changed twice in our 5 night stay. The tv was located on an island in the middle of the room. There was no mini bar in the room but a some store was open very late at night--very convenient. We had plenty of towels. The housekeeping staff replaced shampoo and soap. The bathroom itself could really use some updating. In the bathroom, there was a space where there most likely was a set of shelves--it seemed wierd open and the floor and molding were in disrepair there. Newspapers were available at the consierge desk and cabs easily hailed by the bell staff. Check in and check out were quick. We did not get to the pool but it looked nice. The food and service in the sports bar were good. I ordered room service on a Friday night. It came quickly, the server was very polite and friendly, and the food was really good. This hotel adjoins the Miami Convention Center (our convention was not located here). We did walk through this convention center to take the Metro Mover on Saturday morning. A free and interesting idea, the map is a bit confusing for newbies. Saw security twice and there were cameras everywhere. I was a bit freaked but frankly, it's cleaner than NY subways and probably safe--I'm just not used to it. We had a convention rate but had to pay the full rate of $269 on our last night which was a Saturday night. Having stayed in hotels of the same and better caliber in several major cities, my feeling is this is too high for this particular hotel. 
