<Content>In need of a renovation Stayed at this hotel Feb 20-23, 2006 after canceling reservation at Intercontinental.Stay was for business. Arrived a Miami international. Drive from airport is 20 minutes or less. Construction is terrible around airport and traffic around Miami downtown is similar to that of other large cities. It's not too go. So don't be in a hurry for a meeting. Allow yourself enough time to get to the hotel from the airport.Check-in was quick. Lobby is lackluster at best. Valet was quick and cost $23 a day. Self-park is not convenient at this hotel. Room was on the 23rd floor with Bay view. This is also the floor of the Regency club. This is a very small area that provides continental breakfast for select guests and evening snacks. Nothing to write home about.The room was clean with signs of obvious wear. Room and hotel is dated and in need of serious renovations. The outside temperature averaged low 80's during my stay. The room was always comfortable. The hotel offers Wi-Fi through T-mobile Hot Spot. I'm not a fan of the service because the signal was always weak and you have to use a credit card vs the 9.99 per day being charged to your room.I had a double room. The bed was quite comfortable. Nothing spectacular. Outside of the Regency room, I did not attempt any of the hotels amenities. I used concierge for some directions. The lady that assisted me was great. The staff at the hotel was very pleasant. I would definitely rate them Excellent.Others in my group stayed at the Intercontinental. Views from their rooms were of the bay, Port of Miami, and South Beach, Bayside, etc. Views were very nice. Externally and in the lobby, the hotel was more appealing. Because the hotel is across the street from the park, there is free parking that is very convenient. I'm sure on weekends it would be difficult to find a spot. However, there is a garage right next door as well.We utilized the tram from the hotel to Bayside for dinner. When returning from Bayside, we took a taxi for $5. The drive is no more than five minutes. However, downtown is pretty deserted after business hours. I did not feel comfortable walking from Bayside to the Hyatt. If I stayed at the Intercontinental, I would have walked as it is literally across the park.If I had to, I would stay at the Hyatt again. Overall, it was an OK stay. 
